                  hindlimb backward stepping, while injection of AMPA
                  (0.5 microg) into the core produced only a marginal
                  effect. This shell-specific AMPA effect was
                  dose-dependently inhibited by the AMPA receptor
                  antagonist, NBQX (1 and 10 ng), which alone did not
                  produce turning behaviour. The AMPA-induced pivoting
