                  pivoting. The dopamine D(1)/D(2) receptor
                  antagonist, cis-(Z)-flupentixol (1 and 10 microg),
                  injected into the shell, in doses known to block
                  dopamine D(1)/D(2) receptor-mediated pivoting, also
                  significantly inhibited AMPA (0.5 microg)-induced
