                  concluded that unilateral stimulation of AMPA
                  receptors in the shell of the nucleus accumbens can
                  elicit contraversive pivoting, and that both AMPA
                  and dopamine D(1)/D(2) receptors play a critical
                  role in shell-specific pivoting in contrast to NMDA
